      "content": [
        {
          "type": "thinking",
          "thinking": "Now I have all the information I need. Let me compare the standards:\n\n**差旅住宿标准 (Travel Accommodation Standards)** - from 04_travel_expense.md:\n- Based on employee level AND city tier\n- Employee level: 员工级 一类城市 450, 二类城市 380, 三类城市 300\n- Manager level: 经理级 一类城市 650, 二类城市 550, 三类城市 450\n- Department head level: 部门负责人级 一类城市 850, 二类城市 700, 三类城市 600\n- Senior management level: 高管级 一类城市 1100, 二类城市 900, 三类城市 750\n\n**培训住宿标准 (Training Accommodation Standards)** - from 05_training_expense.md:\n- Only based on city tier (no employee level distinction)\n- 一类城市 500元/人/晚\n- 二类城市 420元/人/晚\n- 三类城市 350元/人/晚\n\nKey differences:\n1. **Basis of determination**: Travel standards vary by employee level AND city tier; training standards vary ONLY by city tier.\n2. **Rate differences**: Training accommodation rates are generally higher than employee-level travel rates but lower than manager-level travel rates. For example:\n   - 一类城市: 培训500 vs 差旅员工450/经理650\n   - 二类城市: 培训420 vs 差旅员工380/经理550\n   - 三类城市: 培训350 vs 差旅员工300/经理450\n\nWhy they can't be mixed:\n- Per 05_training_expense.md Article 6: \"培训住宿标准仅适用于培训期间住宿,不得与差旅住宿标准混用。\"\n- Per 04_travel_expense.md Article 7: \"培训期间住宿不适用本办法住宿表,应按《XX证券培训费管理办法》执行。\"\n- The two standards have fundamentally different bases: travel accommodation is tiered by employee level, while training accommodation is a single rate per city tier regardless of level.\n- Mixing could lead to either over-reimbursement (if someone uses higher standards inappropriately) or under-reimbursement.\n\nThis is a policy question (制度问答题), not an anomaly detection question, so anomaly_ids should be empty.",
          "signature": ""
        },
